  "name": "John 8:1–11",
  "localizedName": "John 8:1–11",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Law of Moses said that people mustn’t commit adultery. Both the man and the woman who were guilty of adultery had to be put to death."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108050",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Pharisees"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " caught a woman committing adultery. This meant that they would have caught the man at the same time. But they never brought the man to Jesus."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The leaders weren’t really interested in the two people or what they did. They wanted to trap Jesus into doing or saying something against the Law of Moses. But Jesus didn’t speak against the Law as they had hoped he would. Instead, he showed them that they were also guilty of sin."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus didn’t judge the woman as guilty. He told her to stop sinning and to live in a way that honoured God."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
